<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<accessibility-service xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    android:accessibilityEventTypes="typeViewScrolled|typeWindowStateChanged"
    android:accessibilityFeedbackType="feedbackGeneric"
    android:notificationTimeout="100"
    android:canRetrieveWindowContent="true"
    android:description="@string/accessibility_service_description"
    />
    <!--
        android:packageNames="com.example.app1, com.example.app2"
        If you want to listen to specific apps, uncomment and list their package names.
        Leaving it out (or setting packageNames to null programmatically) means listen to all.
        For development, listening to all is fine, but for production, you might want
        to let users choose, or have a more focused scope for privacy.

        android:settingsActivity="com.yourname.scrolltrack.SettingsActivity"
        If you have a settings activity for your service, you can specify it here.
    -->